search_results.lyrics:
B61 Lyrics[Verse 1]
He had time on his hands
He carried the world on his shoulders
He said meet me at the Hudson's edge
Help me roll my boulder

[Chorus]
So I went down, running down
Took the B61 across town
To where he was waiting at the ice house
Wish it was my house
He took me out back for a drink
Showed me the heart on his sleeve
[Verse 2]
Love is a daily good thing
I see it in your smolder
But I can't feel it in my hands

[Chorus]
Remember when I went down running down
Took the B61 across town
To wherе you were waiting at the icе house
Wish it was my house
You took me out back for a drink
Showed me the heart on your sleeve

[Bridge]
Like ships in the night
We go down without light
We burn up all our anthracite
And try to make a spark
Find a crack and let it in
It'll come, it might be dim
Adjust your eyes I know you can
You'll find me in the dark
How will I know if I'm the last one alive?
I'm the last one
You might also like[Instrumental Break]

[Verse 3]
For forty-one days and as many nights
I'll be standing where we stood

annotations: The Brooklyn Ice House has a fire pit in the backyard which is often lit in the colder months for patrons.
The Brooklyn Ice House is a bar in Red Hook, Brooklyn. It’s known for its pulled-pork sandwiches, cheap drinks and backyard with a fire pit and picnic tables.
The B61 is a public transit bus in Brooklyn that goes through Red Hook, the location for the meeting of the main character and her lover.

search_results.title: Prodigal Daughter
search_results.lyrics:
Prodigal Daughter Lyrics[Verse 1]
Oh, now Rosie
You come home in the morning
Got a child on your knee and your mother, she looks on
Says “I don’t know that baby 
Don’t know you, why’d you fail me?
You left home seven years ago and I wore black for days.”

[Chorus]
Prodigal daughter returns like a lamb to the slaughter
I know forgiveness won’t come easy, not for you
Look at the child upon my knee
She has eyes of blue
She resembles me resembling you
[Verse 2]
Mama, listen
Come into the kitchen
Pour me some tea, let mе sit at your feet and let me cry
I need a little monеy
I need love, and I need Sunday suppers here at home
Don't want to be alone, let me stay

[Chorus]
Prodigal daughter returns like a lamb to the slaughter
She yearns for the things that you taught her
I know forgiveness won’t come easy, not for me
But I’ll try to shut the past behind us, throw out the key
Give me one more chance to make you see

[Chorus]
Prodigal daughter returns like a lamb to the slaughter
Looking for something in the water
To wash away the the pain
She’s drowning in the painYou might also likeEmbed

description.plain: “Prodigal Daughter” is a twist on the Biblical story of the prodigal son, who is welcomed with open arms by the father he once scorned. Aoife and co-writer Tim O'Brien tell a story of a woman who abandoned her home returning with a child to face her mother, who ultimately rejects her.

annotations: Black and blue all on my face
The “black and blue” could be a reference to fireworks in the night sky. It could also be a physical interpretation of the pain of heartbreak/longing, manifesting itself as bruises.
